Rising Nigerian Afro-pop artiste Kholi, real name Chuwkuemeka Okoli, has released his album, 'Stones to Diamond'. Speaking about it, Kholi said it was written as a personal therapy of changing his path and finding the light. "Each track tackles my journey. I chose the title to symbolise the feeling of security and strength. These two things are foundations from where hope can grow. I hope people can relate to my stories in their own way." Motivated by a desire to make music that goes deeper than entertainment, he is ready to unveil the album. On this project, he dives deep into the topic of love to understand how it feels at it has different stages, including when it has faded away. The album is available on all streaming platforms.